
Data Dictionary: 

Dataset Name: MEP_long.csv

File Description
Trial-level motor evoked potential (MEP) amplitude data in long format. Each row represents a single TMS trial for one participant under one condition and script.

Variables:

Variable ID: participant_id
Variable Name: Participant Identifier
Variable Definition: A unique anonymised identifier assigned to each participant.
Variable Type: Character
Allowable Values: p01, p02, p03, p04, p05, p06
Missing Value Code: N/A — no missing values
Notes: Six participants total. Five of the six participants completed the LSRT script condition.

Variable ID: condition
Variable Name: TMS Condition
Variable Definition: The TMS stimulation condition applied during the trial. TS denotes a single-pulse test stimulus delivered to M1 only. 4ms and 8ms denote paired-pulse TMS with a conditioning pulse delivered to the PPC at 4ms or 8ms interstimulus interval (ISI) prior to the M1 test stimulus.
Variable Type: Character
Allowable Values: TS, 4ms, 8ms
Missing Value Code: N/A — no missing values
Notes: The TS condition serves as the M1-only baseline comparator in all analyses.

Variable ID: mep_amplitude
Variable Name: MEP Amplitude
Variable Definition: The peak-to-peak amplitude of the motor evoked potential (MEP) recorded from the target muscle following TMS, for a single trial recorded in mV. Manually extracted from raw .cfs files using CED Signal; log-transformed for analysis in manuscript R markdown file.
Variable Type: Numeric
Allowable Values: Any positive value (mV); no predefined range
Missing Value Code: N/A — no missing values
Notes: Approximately 18 trials per participant per condition, though trial counts may vary slightly. No missing values.

Variable ID: script
Variable Name: Motor Imagery Script
Variable Definition: The motor imagery script used during the trial. standard refers to a standard motor imagery script. LSRT refers to the Layered Stimulus Response Training guided motor imagery script.
Variable Type: Character
Allowable Values: standard, LSRT
Missing Value Code: N/A — no missing values
Notes: All six participants completed the standard script. Five of the six participants completed the LSRT script.

Raw Data Files:

Location: data/data_raw/
File Types: .cfs and .sgrx
Software: CED Signal
File Description: Paired files containing raw electromyography (EMG) signal data recorded during the TMS experiment. Each .cfs file contains the raw electrophysiological signal data; the accompanying .sgrx file contains the associated Signal software settings and configuration.

Naming Convention: {participant}_{visit}_{ISI}_{script}_{block}
participant: three-digit participant number (e.g., 001)
visit: study visit (e.g., V1, V2)
ISI: interstimulus interval (e.g., 4ms, 8ms)
script: motor imagery script (e.g., standard, lsrt)
block: block number within session (e.g., B1, B2)
Example: 002_V1_4ms_lsrt_B1 — participant 002, visit 1, 4ms ISI, LSRT script, block 1.

Missing Value Code: N/A — no missing values
Notes: Raw data files are not publicly accessible due to the potentially sensitive nature of human participant data.
